    <fr:title text="Monotone Convergence Theorem">Monotone Convergence Theorem</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Theorem</fr:taxon>
    <fr:date>
      <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
      <fr:month>5</fr:month>
      <fr:day>26</fr:day>
    </fr:date>
    <fr:authors>
      <fr:author>Long Nguyen</fr:author>
    </fr:authors>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f_k : \mathbb {R}^d \to  [0, +\infty ]]]></fr:tex> be a sequence of <fr:link type="local" href="FA-0057.xml" addr="FA-0057" title="Measurable function">measurable function</fr:link>s. Assume that</fr:p>
    <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[f_n(x) \leq  f_{n+1}(x) \quad  \text {almost everywhere}]]></fr:tex>
    <fr:p>Then, there exists <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f : \mathbb {R}^d \to  [0, +\infty ]]]></fr:tex> <fr:link type="local" href="FA-0047.xml" addr="FA-0047" title="Measurable set">measurable</fr:link> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f_n \to  f]]></fr:tex> <fr:link type="local" href="FA-0049.xml" addr="FA-0049" title="Almost everywhere">almost everywhere</fr:link>, and</fr:p>
    <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[{\lim _{n \to  +\infty } \int  f_n(x)dx = \int  f(x)dx.}]]></fr:tex>
  </fr:mainmatter>
  <fr:backmatter>
